HEADWORD: Slyboots
<hw>Sly"boots`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A humerous
appellation for a sly, cunning, or waggish person.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Slyboots</qex> was cursedly cunning to hide 'em.</q>
<rj><qau>Goldsmith.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Slyly</ent>⟦br⟧
